{
  "texts": [
    "Determining the right balance between computational effort and the efficiency of hit discovery remains a challenge.",
    "The synthesizability of molecules generated by AI algorithms remains a challenging issue (4, 7, 97, 124).",
    "Despite this, significant progress has been made towards addressing this problem.",
    "New algorithms that can generate molecules more amenable to synthesis and improved methods for evaluating synthesizability, are expected to mitigate this limitation in the near future.",
    "Rule-based systems offer an advantage over trained generative techniques in that they do not require training data and allow the enumeration of the explorable chemical space."
  ]
}